parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames from the engine compartment
or steering column; electrical wires or components melting or burning; loss of power or stalling; unusual noises or smells.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Ignition switch failures can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Difficulty starting the vehicle; key not turning in the ignition; ignition switch malfunctioning; smoke or flames from the steering column or dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failures can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Alternator failure; electrical system malfunctioning; smoke or flames from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission failures can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting gears; clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy; loss of power or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Windshield and seat failures can cause injuries or distractions while driving.
symptoms: Windshield noise or cracking; seat malfunctioning or breaking; difficulty driving due to seat or windshield issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded. In severe cases, engine failure can result in engine fires, which can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants.
Engine fires can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially harm occupants, and lead to accidents or fatalities.

Failure of the vane air flow meter can cause the engine to buck or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded. In snowy conditions, this can cause the front wheels to lock up, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: front wheels locking up in snowy conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the radiator mounts can cause the radiator to lean or rock, leading to damage to surrounding components, such as the alternator case.
Deterioration of the piston rod can cause engine failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the camshaft can cause engine failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the catalytic converter can cause engine performance issues, leading to loss of power, stalling, or engine failure.
The failure of the seatbelt can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: or the buckle won't lock in.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inertia lock shoulder harness can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant's head or body may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: Inertia lock shoulder harness fails to prevent the chin from hitting the steering wheel
or allows the occupant to lunge forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The collapse of the seat back can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly supported.
symptoms: Seat back collapses during an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hood flying open can obstruct the driver's view and lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Hood flies open and damages the windshield.
